We at the Finance Students’ Association focus on constructing and bringing together a mutually-assisting community within finance students of our university.
Providing revision workshops, study groups and the like, we foster connections amongst our cohort, to give you a sense of support and belonging. Through this, we aim to provide our members with higher academic results, better training in valuation and modelling, and importantly, a better university experience.
Club Aims:
To improve members financial modelling and valuation skills;
To provide a platform for members to form study groups for CFA, CPA and FRM exams;
To facilitate social integration between undergraduate students and graduate students;
To cultivate an open environment for the sharing of careers advice highly informed by industry specific experiences, and in relation to the possible career pathways within finance amongst members;
To develop and maintain a club alumni network for the benefit of members seeking career mentorship.
